&lt;p>This entire article is in a question-and-answer format, developed during my own experience implementing Hugo for my work. If you&amp;rsquo;re looking to seriously implement and customize Hugo—and want to avoid the frustration of getting lost in hundreds of videos, articles, or endless searches on ChatGPT or Google—then I recommend reading these two articles. The other article is &lt;a href="https://dasarpai.github.io/dsblog/exploring-go-hugo-framework-part1">here&lt;/a>. Together, they will give you a solid understanding of the entire ecosystem. Even if you&amp;rsquo;re new to website development, you&amp;rsquo;ll gain clarity on how the various components work. At the very least, you&amp;rsquo;ll come away with a valuable set of questions to ask AI during your own implementation.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Saving The Moon</title><link>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/saving-the-moon/</link><pubDate>Wed, 04 Dec 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author><guid>https://dasarpai.github.io/wiaposts/saving-the-moon/</guid><description>&lt;p>
